<h3>The Hybrid Workflow</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Keyword research</strong> — AI-powered tools identified low-to-medium competition keywords with clear search intent</li>
<li><strong>AI drafting</strong> — ChatGPT generated first drafts with target keywords, word counts, and structure</li>
<li><strong>Human editing</strong> — Editors reviewed for factual accuracy, tone alignment, and originality</li>
<li><strong>On-page SEO</strong> — Optimized titles, meta descriptions, internal/external links, H2/H3 structure, alt text, schema markup</li>
<li><strong>Publishing</strong> — Scheduled with consistent cadence</li>
</ol>
<p>The human editing layer added roughly 45 minutes per article. That is 15 hours total for 20 posts. The LLM Visibility experiment spent roughly 5 hours total with minimal editing.</p>
