<p>The traffic growth distributed across multiple pages. No single article carried the load. This is the power of topical authority. When Google sees 800+ indexed pages on related topics, it treats the domain as an authority.</p>
<h3>The Critical Insight</h3>
<p>Edwards noted that Google indexing itself became a quality signal. "Google only indexes content that it thinks is valuable," he wrote. If your AI content is not getting indexed within 14 days, the content is not valuable enough.</p>
<p>This aligns with what we see across our 3,500+ published articles. Indexing rate is the first metric to watch. If it drops below 85%, your content quality has a problem.</p>
<h3>Key Takeaway</h3>
<p>Automation enables rapid testing and scale. But the foundation is keyword selection. Edwards targeted low-competition terms with clear intent. He did not chase high-volume keywords he could not win.</p>
